## 4. Containers — Inspecting & Interacting

```bash
docker ps                     # Running containers
docker ps -a                  # All containers (including stopped)
docker ps -q                  # Only container IDs
docker logs <container>       # View logs
docker logs -f <container>    # Follow logs (live tail)
docker logs --tail 100 <container>  # Last 100 lines
docker inspect <container>    # Full JSON metadata
docker top <container>        # Running processes inside container
docker stats                  # Live resource usage (all containers)
docker stats <container>      # Live resource usage (one container)
docker exec -it <container> bash    # Open shell inside running container
docker exec <container> <cmd>       # Run one-off command inside container
docker cp <container>:/path ./local # Copy file OUT of container
docker cp ./local <container>:/path # Copy file INTO container
docker diff <container>       # Show filesystem changes vs image
docker port <container>       # Show port mappings
docker attach <container>     # Attach terminal to running container's main process
```

