## 5. Dockerfile Instructions (Reference)

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine          # Base image
WORKDIR /app                 # Set working directory
COPY package*.json ./        # Copy files (order matters for caching!)
RUN npm install               # Execute command at build time
COPY . .                      # Copy rest of source
EXPOSE 3000                   # Document the port (doesn't publish it)
ENV NODE_ENV=production       # Set environment variable
ARG BUILD_VERSION=1.0         # Build-time variable (not in final image)
USER node                     # Run as non-root user
VOLUME ["/data"]              # Declare a mount point
CMD ["node", "server.js"]     # Default command (overridable at runtime)
ENTRYPOINT ["node"]           # Fixed entrypoint (args appended to it)
HEALTHCHECK CMD curl -f http://localhost:3000/ || exit 1
```

**CMD vs ENTRYPOINT:** `CMD` can be fully overridden by `docker run <image> <other-cmd>`. `ENTRYPOINT` is fixed; anything passed at runtime is appended as arguments to it. Combine them: `ENTRYPOINT` for the binary, `CMD` for default args.

