## 6. Volumes (Persistent Data)

```bash
docker volume create myvol           # Create a named volume
docker volume ls                     # List volumes
docker volume inspect myvol          # Details (mount point, driver)
docker volume rm myvol               # Remove a volume
docker volume prune                  # Remove all unused volumes

docker run -v myvol:/app/data <image>          # Named volume mount
docker run -v /host/dir:/app/data <image>      # Bind mount (host path)
docker run -v /app/data <image>                # Anonymous volume
docker run --mount type=volume,src=myvol,dst=/data <image>  # Long-form syntax
```

**Volume vs bind mount:** volumes are managed by Docker (`/var/lib/docker/volumes/...`), portable, and preferred for production data. Bind mounts point to a specific host path — great for local dev (live code reload).

