## 7. Networks

```bash
docker network ls                          # List networks
docker network create mynet                # Create a bridge network
docker network create --driver bridge mynet
docker network inspect mynet                # Details (connected containers, subnet)
docker network rm mynet                     # Remove a network
docker network connect mynet <container>    # Attach running container to network
docker network disconnect mynet <container> # Detach

docker run --network mynet --name app1 <image>
docker run --network mynet --name app2 <image>
# app1 can now reach app2 via hostname "app2"
```

Default network types: `bridge` (default, isolated per host), `host` (shares host's network stack), `none` (no networking), `overlay` (multi-host, used in Swarm).

