## 10. Docker Swarm (Orchestration Basics)

```bash
docker swarm init                     # Initialize a swarm (manager node)
docker swarm join --token <token> <manager-ip>:2377   # Join as worker
docker node ls                        # List nodes in swarm
docker service create --name web --replicas 3 -p 80:80 nginx
docker service ls                     # List services
docker service scale web=5            # Scale replicas
docker service update --image nginx:latest web
docker stack deploy -c docker-compose.yml mystack   # Deploy a stack
docker stack services mystack
docker stack rm mystack
```

---

## 11. Cleanup Cheat Sheet (use with care)

```bash
docker container prune       # Remove all stopped containers
docker image prune -a        # Remove all unused images
docker volume prune          # Remove all unused volumes
docker network prune         # Remove all unused networks
docker system prune -a --volumes  # Nuke everything unused
```

---

## 12. Useful Flags Quick Reference

| Flag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `-d` | Detached (background) |
| `-it` | Interactive + TTY (for shells) |
| `-p host:container` | Port mapping |
| `-v host:container` | Volume/bind mount |
| `-e KEY=val` | Environment variable |
| `--name` | Container name |
| `--rm` | Auto-remove on exit |
| `--network` | Attach to network |
| `-f` | Follow (logs) / force (rm) |
| `--build-arg` | Pass build-time variable |
| `--no-cache` | Skip build cache |

